msgSnippet: Hi Mitch, ... Thanks for the feedback  - I ll review and revise in the next day or so; [utter] and [foot] are common errors for me  :-(   - my midland accent
messageBody:
Hi Mitch,


> There were a few places where you wrote with [utter]
> instead
> of [foot]. "books", for example. As you wrote it,
> it sounds
> to me like "bucks".

Thanks for the feedback - I'll review and revise in
the next day or so; [utter] and [foot] are common
errors for me :-( - my midland accent tends to blur
all vowels into either 'schwa' or [utter] if I'm not
careful!

Thanks for taking the time to read - I'll try again
soon,

cheers,
Michael
